\ul \ulc0 The Holocene And the Agro-Pastoral Emergence\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa120

\b\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd3\expndtw15
\ulnone ABSTRACT
\f1\b0 \kerning1\expnd3\expndtw15
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

\f0\fs20 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This lecture introduces the concept known as the Holocene, a climactic condition that began around 10,000 BCE. As a result of the global warming, we see the emergence of several new cultural formations. One of these is the salmon culture that spanned the northern half of the Pacific from the Jomon in Japan to the Haida in Canada. Meanwhile, in North Africa and West Asia, we see the emergence of pastoral and agro-pastoral traditions. The lecture compares the different house and settlement types.
